# CTA Management Guidelines

## Core CTA Principles

### 1. CTA Hierarchy
Maintain clear hierarchy in call-to-action elements:
- **Primary CTA**: Main conversion action (contact, consultation)
- **Secondary CTA**: Supporting actions (learn more, explore)
- **Tertiary CTA**: Navigation aids (view all, see more)

### 2. Visual Priority
Use visual design to establish CTA importance:
```tsx
// Primary CTA - Gradient with shadow
<Button className="bg-gradient-to-r from-primary to-secondary hover:from-primary/90 hover:to-secondary/90 shadow-lg hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300">
  Primary Action
</Button>

// Secondary CTA - Outline with hover
<Button variant="outline" className="border-primary/30 text-primary hover:bg-primary/5 hover:border-primary/50">
  Secondary Action
</Button>

// Tertiary CTA - Text link with icon
<Link className="inline-flex items-center text-primary hover:text-secondary font-semibold">
  View All <ArrowRight className="ml-2 h-4 w-4" />
</Link>
```

## CTA Placement Rules

### 1. Footer CTA Conditional Display
The main footer CTA should only appear on specific pages to avoid overwhelming users:

```tsx
// components/layout/footer.tsx
"use client"
import { usePathname } from "next/navigation"

export default function Footer() {
  const pathname = usePathname()
  const showCTA = pathname === "/" || pathname === "/contact"
  
  return (
    <footer>
      {showCTA && (
        <div className="cta-section">
          {/* Large promotional CTA */}
        </div>
      )}
      {/* Regular footer content */}
    </footer>
  )
}
```

**Pages that should show footer CTA:**
- Home page (`/`)
- Contact page (`/contact`)

**Pages that should NOT show footer CTA:**
- Service pages (`/services/*`)
- Solution pages (`/solutions/*`)
- About pages (`/about`, `/team`)

### 2. Section CTA Limits
Limit CTAs within page sections to maintain focus:
- **Maximum 1 primary CTA per section**
- **Maximum 2 total CTAs per section**
- **Space CTAs at least 100px apart vertically**

### 3. Page-Level CTA Strategy

#### Home Page
- Hero section: 1 primary CTA
- Each major section: 1 CTA maximum
- Footer: Large promotional CTA

#### Service Pages
- Hero section: 1 primary + 1 secondary CTA
- Service cards: Individual explore buttons
- Bottom section: 1 consultation CTA
- Footer: NO promotional CTA

#### Landing Pages
- Hero: 1 primary CTA
- Feature sections: Tertiary CTAs only
- Bottom: 1 primary CTA

## CTA Content Guidelines

### 1. Action-Oriented Language
Use clear, action-oriented text:
```
✅ Good CTA Text:
- "Schedule Free Consultation"
- "Get Security Assessment"
- "Start Protection Now"
- "Explore Peregrine"

❌ Poor CTA Text:
- "Click Here"
- "Submit"
- "Learn"
- "Go"
```

### 2. Value Proposition
Include benefit or value when possible:
```tsx
// With value proposition
<Button>Get Free Security Assessment</Button>
<Button>Schedule Expert Consultation</Button>

// Service-specific value
<Button>Start 24/7 Protection with Peregrine</Button>
<Button>Begin Vulnerability Testing</Button>
```

### 3. Urgency and Scarcity (Use Sparingly)
Only use urgency when genuine:
```tsx
// Acceptable urgency
<Button>Schedule Today - Limited Slots</Button>

// Avoid fake urgency
<Button>Act Now - Offer Expires Soon!</Button>
```

## Service-Specific CTA Patterns

### 1. Service Cards
Each service card should have its own explore button:
```tsx
<Card>
  <CardContent>
    {/* Service content */}
    <Button className={`bg-gradient-to-r ${serviceGradient}`}>
      Explore {serviceName}
      <ArrowRight className="ml-2 h-5 w-5" />
    </Button>
  </CardContent>
</Card>
```

### 2. Individual Service Pages
Structure CTAs in this order:
1. Hero section: Primary action + secondary
2. Services grid: No CTAs (focus on information)
3. Stats section: No CTAs
4. Bottom: Consultation CTA

```tsx
// Hero CTAs
<div className="flex gap-4">
  <Button>Start {ServiceName} Now</Button>
  <Button variant="outline">Learn More</Button>
</div>

// Bottom CTA
<Button>Schedule {ServiceName} Consultation</Button>
```

## CTA Analytics and Testing

### 1. UTM Parameters
Add tracking parameters to measure CTA effectiveness:
```tsx
<Link href="/contact?utm_source=services&utm_medium=cta&utm_campaign=peregrine">
  Contact Us
</Link>
```

### 2. Service-Specific Parameters
Track which service drove the conversion:
```tsx
<Link href="/contact?service=peregrine&source=hero">
  Get Peregrine Protection
</Link>
```

### 3. A/B Testing Considerations
Test different CTA variations:
- Button text
- Color schemes
- Placement
- Number of CTAs

## Mobile CTA Considerations

### 1. Touch Target Size
Ensure CTAs are touch-friendly:
```tsx
// Minimum touch target
<Button className="min-h-[44px] px-6 py-3">
  Touch-Friendly CTA
</Button>
```

### 2. Sticky CTAs for Mobile
Consider sticky CTAs for long pages:
```tsx
// Mobile sticky CTA
<div className="fixed bottom-4 left-4 right-4 z-50 md:hidden">
  <Button className="w-full">
    Primary Mobile Action
  </Button>
</div>
```

### 3. Mobile CTA Stack
Stack CTAs vertically on mobile:
```tsx
<div className="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
  <Button className="w-full sm:w-auto">Primary</Button>
  <Button variant="outline" className="w-full sm:w-auto">Secondary</Button>
</div>
```

## CTA Accessibility

### 1. Screen Reader Support
Provide descriptive labels:
```tsx
<Button aria-label="Schedule a free cybersecurity consultation with our experts">
  Get Consultation
</Button>
```

### 2. Keyboard Navigation
Ensure proper focus management:
```tsx
<Button className="focus:ring-2 focus:ring-primary focus:outline-none">
  Accessible CTA
</Button>
```

### 3. Color Contrast
Maintain WCAG compliance:
- Text contrast ratio ≥ 4.5:1
- Focus indicators must be visible
- Don't rely solely on color for meaning

## CTA Performance Monitoring

### 1. Key Metrics
Track these CTA metrics:
- Click-through rate (CTR)
- Conversion rate
- Bounce rate after CTA click
- Time to conversion

### 2. Conversion Funnel Analysis
Map CTA performance through funnel:
```
CTA Click → Landing Page → Form Fill → Conversion
```

### 3. Heat Map Analysis
Use heat maps to understand:
- Which CTAs get most attention
- Scroll depth before CTA interaction
- Mobile vs desktop behavior differences

## CTA Maintenance Rules

### 1. Regular Audits
Conduct monthly CTA audits:
- Check for broken links
- Verify tracking parameters
- Test responsive behavior
- Review conversion data

### 2. Content Updates
Keep CTA text current:
- Update seasonal offers
- Refresh value propositions
- A/B test new messaging
- Remove expired promotions

### 3. Technical Maintenance
Ensure CTAs remain functional:
- Test across browsers
- Verify mobile behavior
- Check loading performance
- Validate analytics tracking

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid

### 1. CTA Overload
❌ Don't overwhelm users:
- Multiple CTAs competing for attention
- CTAs without clear hierarchy
- Too many options causing paralysis

### 2. Generic CTAs
❌ Avoid non-specific language:
- "Click here"
- "Submit"
- "Read more"
- "Continue"

### 3. Misleading CTAs
❌ Don't deceive users:
- False urgency
- Hidden costs after click
- Mismatched expectations
- Bait-and-switch tactics

